# CODEOWNERS — auto-requests a reviewer when a PR touches matching paths.
# Spreads review load across the team so no one is skipped and no one is buried.
# Replace the placeholders with real @github-usernames once your team is set.
#
# Syntax: <path>   <@owner> [<@owner2> ...]
# More specific lines win. Every PR still needs 1 approval from a non-author.

# Default owner for everything (fallback) — set to the week's Anchor:
# *                     @team-anchor

# Split ownership across members so reviews rotate naturally:
# /src/frontend/        @member-a @member-b
# /src/backend/         @member-c @member-d
# *.md                  @member-e
# /.github/             @team-anchor
